  "texts": [
    "Traditional approaches such as sensory panels rely on human perception to assess aroma and flavor.",
    "While grounded in biological realism, these panels are inherently subjective, often producing variable results across different individuals or sessions.",
    "Factors such as fatigue, training level, and cultural background can influence sensory judgment, making reproducibility a concern.",
    "Chemical analysis methods, including gas chromatography and mass spectrometry, provide highly specific results and allow compound-level identification.",
    "However, these techniques are labor-intensive, require sophisticated equipment, and demand expert interpretation."
  ],
